                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/6–2844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-06T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 6, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>409. In view of recommendations contained in your 464 June 28, you should take
                    early occasion to inform your British and Soviet colleagues that the United
                    States Government does not perceive any necessity for its participation in the
                    proposed Allied-Iranian agreement on financial responsibility for operation of
                    Iranian railways.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
